<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-05T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="925" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/1124a:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-05T21:00:00-04:00">June
                                        5, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>510. British Embassy here has informed Department of telegraphic
                                correspondence between your British colleague and Foreign Office in
                                connection with passage of German ships through Straits and relation
                                of protest on this development to exchange of notes referred to in
                                Department’s 494, June 1. Department assumes that you will act in
                                concert with your British colleague and take no independent action
                                with respect to exchange of notes until his existing instructions
                                have <pb facs="0872" n="860" xml:id="pg_860"/> been confirmed or
                                altered. In latter case Department will promptly instruct you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>